    <body>

      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p><rs type="material">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">block</rs>s making up the Odeon/Bouleuterion stage edge, which is <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.10</measure> high. The rim was broken in several places: it has been largely restored, but four fragments are still loose.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>Cut along the rim of the stage. The total length of the text is <measure type="length" dim="none" unit="metre" precision="circa">7.65</measure>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.06-0.07</measure>; scroll for abbreviation; well cut.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0434" notAfter="0467">Mid fifth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<ab>
		<lb n="1"/><w lemma="ἐπί">ἐπὶ</w> <w lemma="εὐτυχία">εὐτυχίᾳ</w> <w lemma="ὁ"><unclear reason="undefined">τ</unclear>ῆς</w> <rs key="clarus" type="dignity"><w lemma="λαμπρός">λαμπρᾶς</w></rs> <w lemma="Ἀφροδεισιεύς"><placeName type="ethnic" full="yes" reg="Ἀφροδεισιεύς">Ἀφροδισιαί<supplied reason="lost">ων</supplied></placeName></w> <rs key="capital" type="subject"><w lemma="μητρόπολις"><supplied reason="lost">μητροπό</supplied><seg type="fragment">λεω</seg><supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></w></rs> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="οὗτος"><supplied reason="lost">το</supplied>ῦτο</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸ</w> <w lemma="ἔργον">ἔργον</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῆς</w> <w lemma="παλαίστρα">πα<unclear reason="damage">λ</unclear>έσ<unclear reason="damage">τ</unclear><seg type="fragment">ρας</seg></w> <w lemma="γίγνομαι">ἐγέν<supplied reason="lost">ετο</supplied></w> <w lemma="ἐπί"><supplied reason="lost">ἐπὶ</supplied></w> <persName type="aphrodisian" key="Ampelius" full="yes"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low"><name reg="Φλάβιος">Φλαβίου</name></supplied> <supplied reason="lost"><name reg="Ἀμπέλιος">Ἀμπελίου</name></supplied></persName> <w lemma="ὁ"><unclear reason="damage">τ</unclear>ο<supplied reason="lost">ῦ</supplied></w> <w lemma="ἐλλόγιμος"><rs type="dignity" key="eloquentissimus"><expan><abbr>ἐλλογιμ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ωτάτου</supplied></expan></rs></w> <seg type="fragment"><w lemma="σχολαστικός"><rs key="scholasticus" type="profession"><expan><abbr>σχ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ολαστικοῦ</supplied></expan></rs></w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w></seg> <rs key="pater" type="official-secul"><w lemma="πατήρ"><seg>π</seg><supplied reason="lost">ατρ</supplied>ός</w></rs> <w lemma="ἰνδικτιών"><expan><abbr>ἰνδ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ικτιῶνι</supplied></expan></w> <num value="10"><hi rend="supraline">ι</hi></num> <w lemma="εὐτυχής"><expan><abbr>εὐτυχ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">εστάτῃ</supplied></expan></w>
		</ab>
		</div>

      <div type="apparatus">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p><foreign lang="grc">ἰνδ<supplied reason="abbreviation">ικτίωνος</supplied> <num value="10"><hi rend="supraline">ι</hi></num>, εὐτυχ<supplied reason="abbreviation">ῶς</supplied></foreign> ALA;
		<foreign lang="grc">ἰνδ<supplied reason="abbreviation">ικτιῶνι</supplied> <num value="10"><hi rend="supraline">ι</hi></num> εὐτυχ<supplied reason="abbreviation">εστάτῃ</supplied></foreign> Feissel.</p>
        <p>The letters on the loose fragments are highlighted in the text.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>For the good fortune of the splendid metropolis of the Aphrodisians, this work of the <term lang="la">palaestra</term> also took place <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">under Flavius Ampelius</supplied> the most eloquent <term lang="la">scholasticus</term> and <term lang="la">pater</term>, in the tenth indiction. With good fortune.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="IV.21">IV.21</xref> following.</p>
        <p>For Ampelios, see also <xref type="inscription" n="38" href="040202">4.202</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="22" href="120101">12.101</xref> and <xref type="inscription" n="44" href="080609">8.609</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs key="Boul" type="monuList">Bouleuterion/Odeon</rs>: on the stage rim; .</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Findspot.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot; fragments in Museum (1977).</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
